<i><br>Keenedge of E'ci
<br>Vesparo of Vallon Zek
<br>Assassins of the Order of the Ebon Mask</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kendrick>Kendrick</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Grandfather Rogue</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/15/01 2:05:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2014.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: JUST in from Aradune!!!!</span><hr size=1> Darth, experience is still based on the NPC, everything else is just a modifier.<br>
<br>
As far as Warriors and Rogues keeping the bonus, we didn't want to nerf anyone. <br>
<br>
You can bet your sweet patootie that if we did normalize rogues and warriors, there'd be a dozen million threads whining about it. <br>
<br>
And there are those that will argue that since hybrids and monks no longer pay the price for the versatility and abilities they used to, they are now a better bang for the buck than a warrior or rogue.  <br>
<br>
Keeping the bonus for warriors and rogues will help offset this perceived value increase in hybrids. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utelurinon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Telurinon</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_purplespot.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/15/01 3:46:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2014.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/celondon/TelurinonClose.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: JUST in from Aradune!!!!</span><hr size=1> The additional experience bonus is a great idea in some dungeons, yet in some others it is only a first step in making them more popular.<br>
<br>
Najena, for instance, is a very good low level dungeon -- except for two things.  First, the spawn times are hideously long (off hand, I believe it is 30 minutes there -- an 18 minute spawn cycle would seem more appropriate).  Second, the 'Boss' mobs of the place are significantly too strong for the level of the dungeon.  The Widowmistress cannot be taken down by a group that still gets experience for the mobs they must fight to get to her.  Najena herself can be, but it is not an easy task.  Especially if the other Magicians are up in her room.<br>
<br>
Sol A is a GREAT dungeon, and hopefully this new xp mod will popularize it once more.  It is also one of the more popular Farming spots, though, so I can see there being problems that will strain the PNP rules.<br>
<br>
All in all, this is a great first step.  I hope VI looks at the results and determines what their next step will be soon. <p><SELECT NAME="D1">
