<OPTION>Geez, how many characters do you think I have?</SELECT><br><b>Backstab Watch!</b><br><img src=http://www.geocities.com/celondon/BSWatch.jpg><BR><BR>Skating away on the thin ice of a new day.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uderringer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Derringer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/15/01 7:04:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2014.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: JUST in from Aradune!!!!</span><hr size=1> Although I agree that it is the right thing to do, I think it could and should be the first in a line of steps to fix some gameplay problems affecting the high level game.<br>
<br>
Also, Kendrick, I don't believe the previous patch affected the 'bang for the buck' of Hybrids very much, and although this one puts them on a level playing field exp wise, I still don't believe they are on a level playing field in desirability.<br>
<br>
I still see people saying that although the exp constraints of having a hybrid in the group are gone, they still don't offer the group the efficiency of a warrior/rogue.<br>
<br>
If there is any uproar on 'bang for the buck' increases with Hybrids, I have yet to see it, and would be wholly surprised if it ever happened.  I think most reasonable, unbiased, high level warrior/rogues understand the issues quite clearly.  It seems that just recently it is permeating up to the designers.  A step in the right direction? Yes.  Problem fully solved? No. <p>Derringer Labyrinth
58 Knight of Pak'Cafan
Tarew Marr</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usabishi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sabishi</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/15/01 8:07:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2014.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.netvigator.com/~tsoiy/sabishi2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: JUST in from Aradune!!!!</span><hr size=1> The 3 hours limit on rez does have a reason.  I remember there was no time limit on rez and whenever I zoned into Sol B or L Guk, I was greeted by 10+ corpses.  People died and left their corpses at entrance so that they could get a rez later.<br>
<br>
Ah.. the old time..<br>
